Senior night information for fall activities:

Tomorrow 9/11, is senior night for football, band, and cross country. The senior night festivities will start at 6:20 pm, and we ask that the seniors and parents/guardians are at the north entrance to the football field by 6:15.

For our football players, band members, cross country members, and football cheerleaders who can't be there tomorrow, we will be introducing them before the varsity football game on 10/2. We will start the senior night festivities at 6:30 that night, and ask that everyone be at the north entrance to the football field by 6:25 that evening.

Lastly, our volleyball senior night has been rescheduled to 9/21. We will introduce the seniors before varsity warm ups start. We ask that senior players and parents are in the high school commons by 7 pm that evening.

Hello Wildcat country! I just tested out a facebook live video stream in our crows nest and it worked pretty well.

Our goal is to now stream our home varsity home games going forward using Facebook Live until a YouTube channel is set up.

My plan right now is to do a test run Thursday with the freshman and jv volleyball games starting at 5 pm.

We will also broadcast Friday night’s varsity football game vs Wilton. More information to follow as to when the stream will start, but we will include the senior night introductions before the game.

Please share this to all your family and friends who want to follow Wildcat athletics but aren’t able to attend the games, and encourage them to follow the Durant Community School District Facebook page.

Due to the heat and scheduled early outs from school there will be a few changes to our junior high sports practices this week.

Volleyball:
7th and 8th grade volleyball practice will be from 6:30-7:45 Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday of this week. Practices are not mandatory if students do not have transportation, but the girls are encouraged to attend if at all possible.

Football:
Junior high football practice will be right after school dismisses this week. Wednesday-equipment will be handed out and then they are free to leave.
Thursday- They will practice until 3 pm.
Friday-Normal practice time unless we have an early out, then practice will be done by 3 pm.
These practices are not mandatory if students do not have transportation, but the boys are encouraged to attend if at all possible.

Also attached are the forms the student athletes need to have completed to participate. Any student athlete that has not had a physical since July 1, 2019 must have a new physical.

As a way of trying to ensure that our seniors have their senior nights, we have moved these dates forward in the calendar.

Football, cross country, band, and football cheer will have their senior night prior to the football game on Friday 9/11. Homecoming introductions will take place at halftime.

Volleyball will have their senior night at our home volleyball game on 9/10.

Also at football games this year because of social distancing measures, The entire south section of bleachers will be used as our student section, to allow our students to sit and cheer from the same area while also allowing for more social distancing.

The band will be playing from behind the fence in the south end zone. Please make sure kids are not running around in this area during the games.

post_text:
Attached are guidelines for RVC volleyball this fall.
Masks are required to attend our indoor activities.

Other Durant fall sports expectations:

1) Admission will be taken at all sporting events
2) Coolers are not allowed in to our events. Concessions will be available but may be limited to prepackaged food. (We are working on this.)
3) Masks are not required at our outdoor events but are recommended.
4) Practice social distancing. (For volleyball IGHSAU guidelines recommend no spectator seating in the first 2 rows of bleachers if possible. We ask that only people with mobility issues sit in these rows.)
5) Only service animals are allowed at our events. If it's not a service animal please keep it at home!

Wildcat Parents,

Thank you so much for your patience during our internet and JMC outage. As of this morning, both are back up and running! We have extended registration through Monday, August 17th, which includes waiving the service fees.

Please make sure that you have completed all of the registration steps, including the medical questions, choice of virtual, or in-person schooling, and that you have typed your name, as a signature, next to the iPad agreement section.

If you have any difficulties registering, please call the Pre k-12 office at 563-785-4433, and one of the secretaries can help you.

Thank you!

Parents of 7-12th grade athletes planning on participating in fall sports. Please make sure that your child has an updated physical completed prior to the start of fall practices on August 10th. We were not able to offer on campus physicals this spring like we normally would have.

This is the guidance from the state athletic governing bodies regarding sports physicals: "As per the amendment issued by Governor Reynolds on June 25, all physicals signed on or after July 1, 2019 are good through December of 2020."

If the last physical your student athlete had was before July 1, 2019, then they need to get one done to participate.

Final baseball and softball post for the evening...

The River Valley Conference has set up guidelines for our home games this summer. We tried to make these as uniform as possible as a conference, but there are small differences from school to school. Please use this as a reference if you are planning on traveling to any games this summer.

One change to Durant and Wilton from what was originally posted in the Advocate last week:

*** We will NOT be charging admission at our home games this summer*** We will be taking free-will donations at a table set up in between the fields. We still have officials costs to pay for, and without admission and the concession stand bringing in revenue, the athletic department budget will be greatly impacted. We ask that you please consider donating at each game you attend.

post_text:
With baseball and softball games starting tomorrow, here is a little reminder that things will look a little different at our home games this summer. You will see the attached signs at the entrance to the parking lot and around the bleachers.

If you or anyone in your immediate household is displaying symptoms we ask that you not attend the games.

We ask that everyone please adhere to social distancing practices.

Windscreens have been removed from sections of our outfields to allow everyone to spread out.

Per guidance from the IAHSAA and IGHSAU bleacher use is to be limited and marks have been placed on the bleachers to show proper distancing.

Also per guidance from the IAHSAA and IGHSAU there will be no concession stands at our home games this summer. You are welcome to bring coolers of food and beverages to the games, we ask that you just pick up after yourselves.
text:
With baseball and softball games starting tomorrow, here is a little reminder that things will look a little different at our home games this summer. You will see the attached signs at the entrance to the parking lot and around the bleachers.

If you or anyone in your immediate household is displaying symptoms we ask that you not attend the games.

We ask that everyone please adhere to social distancing practices.

Windscreens have been removed from sections of our outfields to allow everyone to spread out.

Per guidance from the IAHSAA and IGHSAU bleacher use is to be limited and marks have been placed on the bleachers to show proper distancing.

Also per guidance from the IAHSAA and IGHSAU there will be no concession stands at our home games this summer. You are welcome to bring coolers of food and beverages to the games, we ask that you just pick up after yourselves.

Dear Durant Families,

In light of the Governor’s decision on April 2, 2020 to extend the closure of school to April 30th because of the COVID-19 virus, the Durant Prom that was going to take place on Saturday, April 25th has been postponed to a later date. The future date for the Durant Prom has not been set yet as the COVID-19 virus situation has yet not stabilized. It is our goal to have the prom even if it extends to a night in the summer. Thank you for your patience and as more details come to light, we will keep you informed. Stay strong and stay safe.



Joel Diederichs

Dear Families,

As many of you may have already heard, the Governor of Iowa has extended our school shut down through April 30th. The Durant Community School District is sharing this information so that you can make appropriate plans for the upcoming weeks.

Please know that iPads can still be picked up on Monday at the scheduled times and our learning opportunities are available for grades PK-12.

If we can be of any assistance to you or your family during this uncharted time, please don’t hesitate to contact the school via email.

Thank you for your continued cooperation and patience - we will all get through this working together!

Joel Diederichs and Rebecca Stineman

** Further Info on the free sack lunch program **
Jeff's Market is happy to help support the Durant and Wilton communities during these trying times by providing free lunches to any community student in need while school is closed due to the covid-19 crisis. If you would like to receive a sack lunch for your child(ren), please call Jeff's Market Durant at 563-785-4767 or Jeff's Market Wilton 563-732-3131 to order your sack lunch so we know how many to make, and we will be happy to get it ready for you.
We will also serve $3 kids hot lunches at Jeff's Market, and $3 baskets at The Creamery (563-785-4950). Feel free to call ahead of time and pick it up (The Creamery even has a drive through).

PLEASE SHARE to help get the word out to families in our community. We are all in this together, please be safe everyone!

With school being out, both Jeff's Market Durant and Wilton, as well as The Creamery will be providing $3 lunches for kids!

At The Creamery choose from a burger, chicken strip, hot dog, or grilled cheese basket for just $3. Feel free to order ahead and pick it up from our drive through window, you do not even need to leave your car!

At Jeff's Market we will be providing $3 chicken lunches for kids! Fried and 2 sides for $3, this can also be called in ahead and picked up at either the Durant or Wilton locations!

Additionally, with school closures and the growing economic impact of covid-19, we would like to help ensure that all children in the community have a hearty lunch. Jeff's Market Durant and Wilton will provide a sack lunch FREE OF CHARGE for child in need. We hope this helps!

post_text:
Meet Joel Diederichs, High School Principal at Durant Community Schools. This is Joel’s 4th year as High School Principal at Durant but it is his 23rd year in the education field. Both of Joel’s parents were educators and growing up he got to hear so many of their former students talk about his how his parents impacted their lives. Joel wanted to be able to carry on that same thing.
Joel is married to his wife, Audra, a social worker and counselor. The role of athletics has played a huge role in Joel’s life as he has coached at various age levels in track, basketball, baseball, and is currently finishing his third season as the varsity head football coach at Durant Community Schools. When he is not on the field with the high school athletes, he is watching or coaching his two boys. Joel enjoys fishing and golfing in his spare time.
“I totally enjoy working with students and watching them succeed both in school and life. “ stated Joel. Joel looks forward to a great year at Durant Community School. “GO Cats!” Thanks for being a leader for our students in Durant, Joel Diederichs!
